																		The hub is live
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/djkaktus" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1888434); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1888434&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610205392" alt="djkaktus" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1888434)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/djkaktus" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1888434); return false;" >djkaktus</a></span> <span class="odate time_1456551172 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">27 Feb 2016 05:32</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2464144">
									

<p>Due to popular demand, the 2016 March Madness challenge (and all subsequent challenges) will operate out of this hub. I have some people to thank for this, so let's start by first thanking:</p>
<p><strong>Decibelle</strong>, whom without I would've never gotten this thing off the ground, last year or this year,</p>
<p><strong>TwistedGears,</strong> who continues to be the voice in my head telling me when I have good or bad ideas,</p>
<p><strong>SunnyClockwork,</strong> who contributed the <em>killer</em> art last year,</p>
<p><strong>Procyonlotor,</strong> who is in the organization channel (bless his heart),</p>
<p>and I'd also like to thank everyone who participated in or helped out with last year's contest, and who have made nominations for this year's contest. Thank you so much.</p>
<p>This year's field was drawn, after careful consideration from the tournament committee, from the list of nominations we received a couple of weeks ago. They're putting in a lot of work to keep this show on the road, and I couldn't do it without them.</p>
<p>Anyway, I'm looking forward to this year, and I hope you are too. See you in March!</p>

							</div>

								
					
